svcRspVersion.name: svcRspVersion
svcRspVersion.description: Description and version number of this module

svcRspPID.name: svcRspPID
svcRspPID.description: Process ID of the svcrsp sub-program.

svcRspModMode.name: svcRspModMode
svcRspModMode.description: This object indicates if the module is in full-mode or restricted-mode. Restricted-mode is entered, when SystemEDGE 4.0 and higher, fails to find a valid license. Once a valid license has been allocated and set, the module will then transition to fullMode(1)

svcRspTable.name: svcRspTable
svcRspTable.description: This table describes the service response time measurements being conducted by this Application Management Moudle.

svcRspTableEntry.name: svcRspTableEntry
svcRspTableEntry.description: An entry in the service response measurement table.

svcRspTableIndex.name: svcRspTableIndex
svcRspTableIndex.description: The index of this service response time table entry

svcRspTableDescr.name: svcRspTableDescr
svcRspTableDescr.description: Description of this service-response monitoring entry. Limit of 256 characters.

svcRspTableSvc.name: svcRspTableSvc
svcRspTableSvc.description: The type of service being measured.

svcRspTableArgs.name: svcRspTableArgs
svcRspTableArgs.description: Service-specific arguments used for measuring purposes. Limit of 256 characters. Example service arguments are: dns: dns-server hostname http: URL [proxy-server] [username:user password:pass] ftp: ftp-server username passwd pop3: pop3-server username passwd nntp: nntp-server smtp: smtp-server ping: system-name packetsize tcpconnect: system-name port custom: script-name https: URL [proxy-server] [username:user password:pass]

svcRspTableInterval.name: svcRspTableInterval
svcRspTableInterval.description: The time interval between queries to the service.

svcRspTableSamplesPerInterval.name: svcRspTableSamplesPerInterval
svcRspTableSamplesPerInterval.description: The number of samples taken at each query interval. For instance, if this value is set to 3 and svcRspTableInterval is set to 60 then after every 60 second interval, 3 sample transactions will be performed.

svcRspTableTimeout.name: svcRspTableTimeout
svcRspTableTimeout.description: The value (in seconds) after which service response time measurement should timeout for this particular service measurement.

svcRspTableStatsWindow.name: svcRspTableStatsWindow
svcRspTableStatsWindow.description: The period (in seconds) over which response time statisics (e.g. mean, availability) for the particular service are calculated.

svcRspTableStatus.name: svcRspTableStatus
svcRspTableStatus.description: The status of this entry. This variable is equivalent in semantics to the SNMPv2 SMI RowStatus convention (see RFC 1443).

svcRspTableLastUpdate.name: svcRspTableLastUpdate
svcRspTableLastUpdate.description: The time (based on sysUpTime) that these counters and statistics were last updated.

svcRspTableNumSamples.name: svcRspTableNumSamples
svcRspTableNumSamples.description: The total number of samples taken since this row was initialized.

svcRspTableTotalLastSample.name: svcRspTableTotalLastSample
svcRspTableTotalLastSample.description: The total response time (in milliseconds) of the last sample.

svcRspTableTotalMin.name: svcRspTableTotalMin
svcRspTableTotalMin.description: The minimum total response time sample value over the statistics window.

svcRspTableTotalMax.name: svcRspTableTotalMax
svcRspTableTotalMax.description: The maximum total response time sample value over the statistics window.

svcRspTableTotalMean.name: svcRspTableTotalMean
svcRspTableTotalMean.description: The mean total response time value over the statistics window.

svcRspTableTotalVariance.name: svcRspTableTotalVariance
svcRspTableTotalVariance.description: The variance of the total response time values over the statistics window * 1000. A variance value of 1.337 would be returned by SA as 1337. The variance is calculated based on seconds, instead of milliseconds.

svcRspTableTotalAvailability.name: svcRspTableTotalAvailability
svcRspTableTotalAvailability.description: The availability of this service. This is calculated as the number of successful service queries divided by the number of service queries over the statistics window. A service query is successful if it succeeds within the timeout value specified for this entry.

svcRspTableNameLastSample.name: svcRspTableNameLastSample
svcRspTableNameLastSample.description: The name lookup (DNS) time (in milliseconds) of the last sample.

svcRspTableNameMin.name: svcRspTableNameMin
svcRspTableNameMin.description: The minimum name lookup time sample value over the statistics window.

svcRspTableNameMax.name: svcRspTableNameMax
svcRspTableNameMax.description: The maximum name lookup time sample value over the statistics window.

svcRspTableNameMean.name: svcRspTableNameMean
svcRspTableNameMean.description: The mean name lookup time value over the statistics window.

svcRspTableNameVariance.name: svcRspTableNameVariance
svcRspTableNameVariance.description: The variance of the name lookup time values over the statistics window. The variance is calculated based on seconds, instead of milliseconds.

svcRspTableConnLastSample.name: svcRspTableConnLastSample
svcRspTableConnLastSample.description: The connection time (in milliseconds) of the last sample.

svcRspTableConnMin.name: svcRspTableConnMin
svcRspTableConnMin.description: The minimum connection time sample value over the statistics window.

svcRspTableConnMax.name: svcRspTableConnMax
svcRspTableConnMax.description: The maximum connection time sample value over the statistics window.

svcRspTableConnMean.name: svcRspTableConnMean
svcRspTableConnMean.description: The mean connection time value over the statistics window.

svcRspTableConnVariance.name: svcRspTableConnVariance
svcRspTableConnVariance.description: The variance of the connection time values over the statistics window. The variance is calculated based on seconds, instead of milliseconds.

svcRspTableTranLastSample.name: svcRspTableTranLastSample
svcRspTableTranLastSample.description: The transaction time (in milliseconds) of the last sample.

svcRspTableTranMin.name: svcRspTableTranMin
svcRspTableTranMin.description: The minimum transaction time sample value over the statistics window.

svcRspTableTranMax.name: svcRspTableTranMax
svcRspTableTranMax.description: The maximum transaction time sample value over the statistics window.

svcRspTableTranMean.name: svcRspTableTranMean
svcRspTableTranMean.description: The mean transaction time value over the statistics window.

svcRspTableTranVariance.name: svcRspTableTranVariance
svcRspTableTranVariance.description: The variance of the transaction time values over the statistics window. The variance is calculated based on seconds, instead of milliseconds.

svcRspTableBytesInLastSample.name: svcRspTableBytesInLastSample
svcRspTableBytesInLastSample.description: The number of bytes received in the last sample.

svcRspTableBytesOutLastSample.name: svcRspTableBytesOutLastSample
svcRspTableBytesOutLastSample.description: The number of bytes sent in the last sample.

svcRspTableTotalBytesIn.name: svcRspTableTotalBytesIn
svcRspTableTotalBytesIn.description: The total number of bytes received since SA was started. It should be noted that this counter will eventually wrap.

svcRspTableTotalBytesOut.name: svcRspTableTotalBytesOut
svcRspTableTotalBytesOut.description: The total number of bytes sent since SA was started. It should be noted that this Counter will eventually wrap.

svcRspTableThroughput.name: svcRspTableThroughput
svcRspTableThroughput.description: The throughput, calculated over the statistics window, in bytes/sec. The BytesInLastSample and BytesOutLastSample will be added together for each sample. This number for each sample will be summed, and divided by the number of seconds in the sample.

svcRspTableResults.name: svcRspTableResults
svcRspTableResults.description: The results of the test. This field indicates non-error results, and the values are specific to each test type.

svcRspTableErrorCode.name: svcRspTableErrorCode
svcRspTableErrorCode.description: The error code returned by the test. The values are specific to each test type. When possible, the standard numeric error codes for each test will be used (e.g. HTTP 404).

svcRspTableTOSField.name: svcRspTableTOSField
svcRspTableTOSField.description: This field allows the user to set the 8-bit TOS header in the IP header for each test. We will not enforce any particular RFC standard for the value of this field. It will be totally up to the user to decide an appropriate value.

svcRspTableFlags.name: svcRspTableFlags
svcRspTableFlags.description: Reserved for future use as a bitmask field for toggle options

svcRspTableLimit.name: svcRspTableLimit
svcRspTableLimit.description: This is the eHealth Response limit, used as a boundry for throwing exceptions

svcRspTableUsername.name: svcRspTableUsername
svcRspTableUsername.description: For tests that require a login, the username is here instead of in the args field as in versions prior to 1.3

svcRspTablePassword.name: svcRspTablePassword
svcRspTablePassword.description: For tests that require a login, the password is here instead of in the args field as in versions prior to 1.3

svcRspTableDest.name: svcRspTableDest
svcRspTableDest.description: For all tests, the target / destination is now stored here instead of in the args field.

svcRspTableTotalErrors.name: svcRspTableTotalErrors
svcRspTableTotalErrors.description: This is the total number of errors, of all types, that this test has encountered over it's lifetime

svcRspTableSamplesInWindow.name: svcRspTableSamplesInWindow
svcRspTableSamplesInWindow.description: This is the total number of samples represented by the status window. A 300 second window on a test with a 30 second interval would be 10, with the exception of during start up, and when a test is thrown out.

svcRspTableSuccessesInWindow.name: svcRspTableSuccessesInWindow
svcRspTableSuccessesInWindow.description: This is the total number of successes within the status window for this test.

svcRspUnusedIndex.name: svcRspUnusedIndex
svcRspUnusedIndex.description: An SNMP Get of this MIB object returns an un-used svcrsp Table index number. It can be used for svcrsp table row creation optimization.

svcRspMatchDescr.name: svcRspMatchDescr
svcRspMatchDescr.description: This MIB object, when used in conjunction with svcRspEventMatchIndex can be used to quickly determine the index number corresponding to a particular entry description. SNMP Set'ing a description to this MIB object causes the agent to search through entries in the svcrsp table and place the index value of the last entry whose description matches, in the svcRspMatchIndex MIB object. If the description is not found, then 0 is placed in svcRspEventMatchIndex.

svcRspNumTests.name: svcRspNumTests
svcRspNumTests.description: This is the number of tests currently running on the agent. This may be greater than the number seen in eHealth, as it includes manually configured tests. This number should never be lower than the number of tests seen in eHealth.

svcRspMaxThreads.name: svcRspMaxThreads
svcRspMaxThreads.description: This is the maximum number of threads that the collector is allowed to run. Each thread executes a test, so multiple threads allows for tests to run concurrently.

svcRspSecurityFlags.name: svcRspSecurityFlags
svcRspSecurityFlags.description: This is a bitmask for displaying various security settings: Bit 0: Security settings hidden. If this bit is set, all others will be set to 0 Bit 1: Allow Custom/Virtual User tests Bit 2: Allow File I/O tests Bit 3: Allow Untrusted SSL certificates in all SSL-based tests Bit 4-32 are currently unused
